er role as Shirley on the live-action sitcom ''[[Laverne & Shirley]]'' in August 1982. Conversely, Williams' role in the animated series was taken over by friend [[Lynne Marie Stewart]]. Only eight episodes were produced. Thus, the existing segments produced up to that point were rerun for the rest of the series. Except for a few publicity cel paintings, no further plans for the series were made.{{citation needed|date=March 2015}}\n\n===Episode list===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#ffffff\"\n|- style=\"color:#ffffff\"\n! style=\"background:#006400; width:20px\"| N\u00ba\n! style=\"background:#006400\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#006400; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L1\n| Title = The Speed Demon Get-Away Caper\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|9|25}}\n| ShortSummary = When Fonz is wrongly imprisoned for a stolen car, Laverne and Shirley (with Squealy) go on a quest to capture the real criminal.\n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L2\n| Title = Swamp Monsters Speak with Forked Face\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|2}}\n| ShortSummary = Laverne and Shirley board a ship to obtain photographic proof of a two-headed swamp monster.\n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L3\n| Title = Movie Madness\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|9}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L4\n| Title = One Million Laughs B.C.\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|16}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L5\n| Title = The Robot Recruit\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|23}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L6\n| Title = All the President's Girls\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|30}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L7\n| Title = Laverne and Shirley and the Beanstalk\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|6}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L8\n| Title = Raiders of the Lost Pork\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|13}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n|}\n\n===Cast===\n* [[Penny Marshall]] - [[Laverne DeFazio]]\n* [[Henry Winkler]] - [[Fonzie|Arthur \"Fonzie\"/\"The Fonz\" Fonzarelli]]\n* [[Lynne Marie Stewart]] - Shirley Feeney\n* [[Kenneth Mars]] - Sgt. Turnbuckle\n* [[Ron Palillo]] - Sgt. {{proper name|Squealy}}\n* [[Frank Welker]] - Mr. Cool\n* [[Michael Bell (actor)|Michael Bell]] \n* [[Val Bettin]] - \n* [[William Callaway]] - \n* [[Philip L. Clarke]] - \n* [[Keene Curtis]] - \n* [[Jeff Doucette]] - \n* [[Richard Erdman]] - \n* [[Helen Hunt]] - \n* [[Julie McWhirter]] - \n* [[Allan Melvin]] - \n* [[Marilyn Schreffler]] - \n* [[Hal Smith (actor)|Hal Smith]] - \n* [[Lennie Weinrib]] -\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0083450}}\n* {{tv.com show|the-mork-and-mindylaverne-and-shirleyfonz-hour|The Mork &amp; Mindy / Laverne &amp; Shirley / Fonz Hour}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fiKN6uRsTM0 The show's opening] on [[YouTube]]\n* ''[http://www.toonarific.com/show.php?s_search=mork+and+mindy&Button_Update=Search&show_id=2474 The Mork & Mindy / Laverne & Shirley / Fonz Hour]'' at Toonarific.com\n* [http://www.bcdb.com/cartoons/Other_Studios/R/Ruby-Spears_Productions/The_Mork__amp__Mindy_-_Laverne__amp__Shirley_-_Fonz_Hour/index.html Episode index]{{Dead link|date=April 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} at the [[Big Cartoon DataBase]]\n\n{{Happy Days}}\n{{Children's programming on the American Broadcasting Company in the 1980s}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mork and Mindy Laverne and Shirley Fonz Hour}}\n[[Category:1982 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1983 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:1980s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by CBS Television Studios]]\n[[