ers from the live-action sitcoms ''[[Mork & Mindy]]'', ''[[Laverne & Shirley]]'' and ''[[Happy Days]]'', all part of the same franchise. This [[Saturday morning cartoon|Saturday morning]] series lasted for one season on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]].<ref name=Daytime>{{cite book |last1=Hyatt |first1=Wesley |title=The Encyclopedia of Daytime Television |date=1997 |publisher=Watson-Guptill Publications |isbn=978-0823083152 |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofda00hyat/page/256/mode/2up|accessdate=19 March 2020|page=257}}</ref>\n\nThis show was divided into two segments: ''Mork & Mindy'' and ''Laverne & Shirley with Special Guest Star The Fonz''. The ''Laverne & Shirley'' half-hour was the second season of ''[[Laverne & Shirley (1981 TV series)|Laverne & Shirley in the Army]]'', with the addition of [[the Fonz]] and his dog Mr. Cool from the earlier cartoon ''[[The Fonz and the Happy Days Gang]]''.<ref name=Perlmutter>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |page=352}}</ref>\n\n==''Mork & Mindy''==\nIn the ''Mork & Mindy'' segment, in which [[Robin Williams]] and [[Pam Dawber]] voiced the title characters, a teenaged Mork is sent to Earth from planet Ork to observe the lives of human teenagers and enroll in a local school. As on the original show, Mindy McConnell and her father Fred (voiced by [[Conrad Janis]]) are the only Earthlings who know that he is an alien and he sends telepathic reports of his experiences to Orkan ruler Orson (voiced by an uncredited [[Ralph James]]). Unlike the original show, Mork is accompanied by his Orkan pet, a pink, six-legged, [[dog]]-like creature named Doing (voiced by [[Frank Welker]]) which is pronounced as \"Doyng\". Other characters in the show included Eugene (voiced by [[Shavar Ross]]), Hamilton (voiced by Mark L. Taylor), and Principal Caruthers (voiced by an uncredited [[Stan Jones (actor)|Stanley Jones]]).\n\n===Episode list===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#ffffff\"\n|- style=\"color:#ffffff\"\n! style=\"background:#B11030; width:30px\"| N\u00ba\n! style=\"background:#B11030\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#B11030; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M1\n| Title = Who's Minding the Brat?\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|9|25}}\n| ShortSummary = Mindy has Mork babysit while she takes her dad to the airport.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M2\n| Title = The Greatest Schmoe on Earth\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|2}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M3\n| Title = To Ork or Not to Ork\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|9}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M4\n| Title = Orkan Without a Cause\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|16}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M5\n| Title = Mork Man vs. Ork Man\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|23}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M6\n| Title = Which Witch Is the Witch\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|30}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M7\n| Title = Every Doing Has His Day\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|6}}\n| ShortSummary = Mork helps Doing earn his way back in the house.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M8\n| Title = Beauty or the Beast\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|13}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M9\n| Title = Morkel and Hyde\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|20}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M10\n| Title = The Wimp\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|27}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B1